oring a “PLAUSIBLE” bearish thesis rather than “PROVEN,” because the market is pricing large moves and headline risk around logistics/weather could cause sharp reversals.\n\nOverall: the bear better satisfies symmetric evidence standards for continuation—multiple fresh, source-specific data points support supply-easing/weakness—while the bull’s reversal call leans more on interpretation and short-term bounce signals that are not independently confirmed as a durable fundamental turn. [Consensus ALIGNED (Vote=BEARISH)] [VOL WARNING: Options expensive. Spread costs elevated. Thesis: PLAUSIBLE]', 'regime': 'HIGH_VOLATILITY', 'volatility_sentiment': 'BEARISH', 'confidence': 0.8, 'price': 275.85, 'sma_200': 301.368, 'expected_price': 275.85, 'predicted_return': 0.0, 'thesis_strength': 'PLAUSIBLE', 'conviction_multiplier': 1.0}]
